arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor WebAssembly PWA for building inspectors on construction sites. The project already exists at `/tmp/sv-e06968a7c6c643b1a6550f214dfd851d/SiteInspector` — it was created with `dotnet new blazorwasm --pwa`. The target framework is net11.0.

Requirements:
- Inspectors fill out safety checklists and add notes at each site visit
- Photos are attached to inspection reports
- Construction sites frequently have poor/no cellular connectivity — the app must work offline
- When connectivity returns, data syncs back to the server
- Mobile-first (phones/tablets)
- Low-latency UI — inspectors tap through checklist items quickly
- No authentication

Architecture decisions:
- Blazor WebAssembly (already set up) for client-side execution
- PWA with service worker for offline asset caching (already scaffolded)
- IndexedDB via JS interop for local data storage (offline-first)
- A sync service that queues and pushes data when online
- Camera access via JS interop for photo capture
- Mobile-first responsive CSS

Please implement the following files. Use the edit tool for files that already exist, create tool for new ones.

## 1. Models (`Models/` directory)

Create `Models/Inspection.cs`:
